questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Match the following government schemes with their focus areas:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;width:500px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Scheme&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Focus Area&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;A. Sarva Shiksha Abhiyan (SSA)&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;1. Universalization of elementary education&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;B. Mid-Day Meal Scheme&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;2. Nutritional support in schools&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;C. Digital India&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;3. Digital infrastructure and services&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;D. SWAYAM&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;4. Online courses and learning&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Option 1&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;width: 500px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Scheme&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Focus Area&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;A. Sarva Shiksha Abhiyan (SSA)&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;1. Universalization of elementary education&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;B. Mid-Day Meal Scheme&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;2. Nutritional support in schools&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;C. Digital India&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;3. Digital infrastructure and services&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;D. SWAYAM&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;4. Online courses and learning&lt;br /&gt;
			&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sarva Shiksha Abhiyan (SSA)&lt;/span&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;SSA was launched in 2001 by the Government of India to ensure that every child receives quality elementary education.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The scheme also focuses on bridging gender and social category gaps at the elementary level.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Mid-Day Meal Scheme&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Launched in 1995, the scheme aims to improve the nutritional status of school-age children nationwide.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It also seeks to increase school enrollment, attendance, and retention while simultaneously improving socialization among children belonging to different social backgrounds.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Digital India&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Digital India was launched in 2015 with the vision to transform India into a digitally empowered society and knowledge economy.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It has three key vision areas: digital infrastructure as a utility to every citizen, governance and services on demand, and digital empowerment of citizens.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;SWAYAM&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;SWAYAM is an initiative by the Government of India designed to achieve the three cardinal principles of education policy, namely, access, equity, and quality.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The objective is to take the best teaching-learning resources to all, including the most disadvantaged.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct answer is - &lt;u&gt;Art. 30&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Article 30&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Article 30 of the Indian Constitution grants minorities the &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;right to establish and administer educational institutions&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; of their choice.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The term &amp;quot;minorities&amp;quot; refers to &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;linguistic&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; or &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;religious minorities&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; as identified under the Constitution.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This article ensures that minority communities can preserve their &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;culture&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;language&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;heritage&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; through educational institutions.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It protects these institutions from discrimination in matters of aid and recognition from the state.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Judicial Interpretations&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Supreme Court of India has consistently upheld the autonomy of minority institutions under Article 30.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;In cases like &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;St. Stephen&amp;#39;s College v. University of Delhi&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, the Court reinforced the rights of minorities to establish institutions without undue interference.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Difference between Articles 29 and 30&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Article 29&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;: Focuses on the protection of the interests of any section of citizens, including minorities, in preserving their &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;language&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;script&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, or &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;culture&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Article 30&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;: Specifically grants &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;rights&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; to minorities to establish and administer educational institutions of their choice.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;While Article 29 is broader and applies to all citizens, Article 30 is exclusive to &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;minorities&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Article 28&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Deals with the &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;freedom from religious instruction&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; in educational institutions funded by the state.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It prohibits religious teachings in such institutions to ensure secularism.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Article 31A&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Primarily relates to the protection of laws that deal with &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;land reforms&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; and is unrelated to educational rights.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It aims to safeguard legislation that strives for equitable distribution of resources.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

questions.statement:
Select the correct statements :&lt;br /&gt;
A. Teachers in HEIs must be strict disciplinarian.&lt;br /&gt;
B. Teachers in HEIs must motivate her learners to learn independently.&lt;br /&gt;
C. Teachers in HEIs must not use any technology.&lt;br /&gt;
D. Teachers in HEls must not interact with students outside classroom.&lt;br /&gt;
E. Teachers in HEIs must be an avid reader and a participant in her discipline&amp;#39;s discourse.&lt;br /&gt;
Choose the correct answer from the options given below:

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct answer is - &lt;u&gt;A, B, C, D, and E&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Teachers in HEIs (Higher Education Institutions)&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Statement A: Teachers in HEIs must be strict disciplinarians because maintaining discipline is crucial for creating a conducive learning environment.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Statement B: Teachers in HEIs must motivate learners to independently learn, fostering critical thinking and self-directed learning skills.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Statement C: The statement that teachers should not use technology is incorrect, as technology is a vital tool in modern education to enhance teaching and learning experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Statement D: Interaction with students outside the classroom is essential for guidance and mentorship, making this statement inaccurate.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Statement E: Teachers must be avid readers and active participants in their field&amp;#39;s discourse to ensure they stay updated with the latest developments and impart quality education.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Role of Teachers in HEIs&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Teachers serve as both educators and mentors, shaping the intellectual and personal growth of students.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Use of technology, such as Learning Management Systems (LMS) and digital tools, is encouraged to enhance the learning experience.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Fostering an environment of independent learning encourages students to develop critical thinking and problem-solving skills.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Importance of Discipline&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Discipline in classrooms ensures a structured and respectful environment conducive to learning.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;However, strict discipline should balance with empathy to maintain a positive teacher-student relationship.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Interaction Outside the Classroom&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Engagement outside the classroom facilitates mentorship, personal guidance, and academic support for students.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Such interactions often help address individual challenges faced by students, enhancing their overall academic experience.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;Which of the following factors the NIRF rankings are based on?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A. Teaching, Learning and Resources (TLR)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;B.&amp;nbsp;Graduation Outcomes (GO)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;C.&amp;nbsp;Research and Professional Practice (RP)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;D.&amp;nbsp;Student Satisfaction (SS)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;E.&amp;nbsp;Peer Perception.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;F.&amp;nbsp;Outreach and Inclusivity (OI)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Select the correct answer from the following codes:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;A, B, C, E and F&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color:  (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;National Institutional Ranking Framework (NIRF):&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color:  (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;National Institutional Ranking Framework is an initiative of the Government of India that was launched in 2015.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The NIRF aims to rank higher educational institutions in India based on various parameters such as teaching, learning, research, outreach, and overall institutional performance.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The framework provides a methodology to evaluate and rank institutions, including universities, engineering colleges, management institutes, pharmacy colleges, and overall institutions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The rankings generated by NIRF are intended to provide valuable information to students, parents, and other stakeholders for making informed decisions about higher education institutions in India.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The NIRF provides for ranking of institutions in five broad generic groups of parameters, namely:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Teaching, Learning and Resources (TLR):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;This parameter measures the quality of teaching and learning at an institution. It considers factors such as the faculty-student ratio, the number of PhD-holders on the faculty, and the availability of library and laboratory resources.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Research and Professional Practice (RP):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;This parameter measures the research output of an institution. It considers factors such as the number of publications in peer-reviewed journals, the number of patents filed, and the amount of external funding received for research.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Graduation Outcome (GO):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;This parameter measures the success of an institution in graduating students who are ready for employment or further study. It considers factors such as the placement rate of graduates, the number of students who go on to earn PhDs, and the number of students who start their own businesses.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Outreach and Inclusivity (OI):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;This parameter measures the efforts of an institution to reach out to and include students from all backgrounds. It considers factors such as the number of students from underrepresented groups, the availability of financial aid, and the availability of support services for students with disabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Peer Perception:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;This parameter measures the reputation of an institution among its peers. It considers factors such as the opinion of academic experts, the opinion of industry leaders, and the opinion of employers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;A, B, C, E and F.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
